ty, and accessibility to readers with little to no prior knowledge of Asian American studies. Featuring both reprints of seminal articles and groundbreaking texts, as well as bold new scholarship, Asian American Studies Now addresses the new circumstances, new communities, and new concerns that are reconstituting Asian America.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aAmerican literaturexAsian American authors. 0aAsian AmericansxHistory. 0aAsian AmericansxSocial conditions. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aAncheta, Angelo N.1 aAncheta, Angelo N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChan, Sucheng, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChan, Suecheng.1 aChen, Thomas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aChiu, Monica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChiu, Monica.1 aDirlik, Arif, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDirlik, Arif.1 aDorow, Sara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDorow, Sara.1 aEng, David L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEng, David.1 aEspiritu, Yen Le, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEspiritu, Yen Le.1 aHan, Shinhee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHan, Shinhee.1 aKim, Elaine.1 aLee, Ericka.1 aLee, Erika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLee, Robert G.1 aLee, Robert G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeong, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeong, Andrew.1 aMaira, Sunaina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaira, Sunaina.1 aManalansan I 